result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Rachel K. Hastings in court with attorney Cana G Kohn.  Jill Laufenberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 16CF195, 16CF213, 16CM101, 16CM168, and 16CM201 @ 10:50 a.m. Agreement stated - Def will plead to 16CF195 ct 1, cts 2-8 dismiss and read in, 16CF213 plea to cts 2 & 5, cts 1, 3, 4, 6-9 dismiss and read in. 16CM101 dismiss and read in, 16CM168 dismiss and read in all cts. 16CF195 ct 1 and 16CF213, ct 2  withheld sentence, 4 yrs probation, 4 months jail, concurrent, AODA and follow through, mental health eval, absolute sobriety, no contct w/ D.G., court costs, DNA. 16CF213 ct 5 - jail, all sentence credit applied to this, sentence complete. Restitution CoVantage $2249.91 in 16CM168 read in. State has complied with victim rights. 16CM201 - dismiss and read in, however, would like to be heard on bond forf. Atty Kohn agrees. Advises 65 days sentence credit. Def agrees. Plea quest. reviewed. (D.A. Elizabeth Constable replaces ADA Laufenberg @ 11:02) 16CF213 ct 2 - no contest, ct 5 - no contest plea. 16CF195 ct 1 - no contest plea. Court grants motions to dismiss 16CM201 cts 1 & 2 dismissed and read in. 16CM168 cts 1-4 dismissed and read in. 16CM101 dismissed and read in. State clarifies restitution is in 16CF195. 16CF213 cts 1, 3, 4, 6-9 dismissed and read in. 16CF195 cts 2-8 dismissed and read in. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Kohn satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 16CF213 cts 2 & 5, 16CF195 ct 1. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. State has complied with victim rights on all cases. Court questions bond poster. Statement by Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court. Will follow agreement. 16CF195 ct 1 - withheld prison sentence, 4 yrs probation, 4 months jail, huber, report no later than 7 p.m. on 12/30/16, AODA and follow through, mental health evaluation and follow through, absolute sobriety, no presence in bars/taverns - anyplace w/class B liquor license, no contact w/D.G. Court costs. DNA sample and surcharge. $2249.91 restitution to Covantage Credit Union - apply from $4,250 bond in 16CM201 - return balance to poster. Return $5000 bond to poster. Court addresses $400 bond being held, ordered forfeited to County. 16CF213 ct 2 - withheld, 4 yrs probation, 4 months jail, concurrent, huber, same conditions, court costs, DNA surcharge. Ct 5 - 65 days jail, credit for time served, sentence complete. Court does not find credit for time if revoked, however, reserves right to be heard if revoked. DNA surcharge, court costs. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. Court orders court costs/DNA surcharge on ct 5 16CF213 be taken from $4250 bond.
